      </div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-4">
        Calculate Your <span class="text-red-600">BC PNP Score</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Get an instant estimate of your SIRS points. 100% free, anonymous, and updated for 2026 British Columbia immigration policies.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-red-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-red-600 font-bold mb-2">1</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Experience</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-red-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-red-600 font-bold mb-2">2</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Education</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-red-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-red-600 font-bold mb-2">3</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Language</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-red-50 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center text-red-600 font-bold mb-2">4</div>
          <span class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Job Details</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- H1 for SEO -->
  <div class="pt-28 pb-4 px-4 sm:px-6 text-center bg-gradient-to-b from-red-50 to-white">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight">
      Free BC PNP <span class="text-red-600">Points Calculator</span> 2026
    </h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-base mt-3 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Calculate your Skills Immigration Ranking System (SIRS) score instantly and find out where you stand for the next BC PNP draw.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Calculator React Island - Hydrated on Load -->
  <CalculatorShell t={calculatorContent.en} />

  <!-- SEO Content Section (Static HTML) -->
  <section
    class="bg-white border-t border-red-100 pt-12 sm:pt-20 pb-32 sm:pb-48 px-4 sm:px-6"
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-12 sm:space-y-20">
      <!-- SEO Intro -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight"
        >
          Using the <span class="text-red-600">BC PNP Calculator</span> for Your Immigration
          Strategy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-base leading-relaxed">
          The British Columbia Provincial Nominee Program (BC PNP) is a
          points-based immigration system designed to attract skilled workers to
          the province. Our <strong>BC PNP points calculator</strong> is an essential
          tool for prospective immigrants to estimate their Skills Immigration Ranking
          System (SIRS) score accurately. By understanding your <strong
            >BC PNP score calculator</strong
          > results, you can make informed decisions about your application strategy.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 pt-4">
          <div class="p-6 bg-red-50 rounded-3xl border border-red-100">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-red-900 mb-2">How Points are Awarded</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
              Points are distributed across economic factors (work experience,
              education, and language) and human capital factors (hourly wage
              and regional location).
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 bg-slate-50 rounded-3xl border border-slate-200">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Maximum Points</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
              The total possible score in the <strong
                >BC PNP point calculator</strong
              > is 200. Most successful candidates score between 100 and 130.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Detailed Scoring Information -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight">
          Point Categories Explained
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="p-8 bg-red-50/50 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-red-100">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-red-900">Work Experience</h3>
              <span class="text-red-600 font-black text-xl">40 pts max</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
