              experience, with additional bonuses for Canadian experience and
              current BC employment.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-slate-600 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>0-5+ years of experience: 0-20 points (4 points per year)</li>
              <li>1+ year Canadian experience: +10 bonus points</li>
              <li>Currently working in BC: +10 bonus points</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-8 bg-rose-50/50 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-rose-100"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-rose-900">Education Level</h3>
              <span class="text-rose-600 font-black text-xl">40 pts max</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Your highest completed credential determines your education
              points. All credentials must be recognized by Canadian standards.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-slate-600 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>PhD/Doctorate: 27 points</li>
              <li>Master's degree: 22 points</li>
              <li>Bachelor's or Post-grad diploma: 15 points</li>
              <li>Associate degree or Certificate: 5 points</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-8 bg-orange-50/50 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-orange-100"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-orange-900">
                Language Proficiency
              </h3>
              <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl">40 pts max</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Based on Canadian Language Benchmark (CLB) levels from approved
              tests like IELTS or CELPIP. Higher proficiency significantly
              boosts your score.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-slate-600 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>CLB 9+: 30 points (Maximum)</li>
              <li>CLB 8: 25 points (Advanced)</li>
              <li>CLB 7: 20 points (Proficient)</li>
              <li>CLB 6: 15 points (Intermediate)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="p-8 bg-red-50/60 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-red-100">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-red-900">Hourly Wage</h3>
              <span class="text-red-600 font-black text-xl">55 pts max</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The highest-weighted category. Your BC job offer's hourly wage is
              the single most important factor in your SIRS score.
            </p>
            <ul class="text-xs text-slate-600 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
              <li>$70.00+/hour: 55 points (Maximum)</li>
              <li>$50.00/hour: 35 points (Competitive)</li>
              <li>$35.00/hour: 20 points (Moderate)</li>
              <li>Below $16/hour: 0 points (No points)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="p-8 bg-rose-50/60 rounded-[2.5rem] border border-rose-100"
